main event: A bright, multi-colored object with jagged outer edges was observed in the sky near St. Marboo, Massachusetts on July 5, 1952.
interesting points: The object appeared to be a bright light that passed through the observer's field of vision.
The colors of the object were described as red, orange, yellow, and blue.
The object was observed for about 20 minutes and appeared to be stationary.
The observer could not account for the color and size of the object.
Astronomers determined the object was likely Saturn, which was in the southwest sky at the time of the sighting.
sighted object: A bright, multi-colored object with jagged outer edges
witnesses: At least one observer, potentially more
